n                        Ἑορτὴ\n                    \">  \u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Καιλία\">Καιλία\u003C/span> · \u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Ἑορτὴ\">Ἑορτὴ\u003C/span>  \u003C/span> · \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>ἐβίωσε · ἔτη · ο’ \u003Cbr id=\"al5-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Βλάστη\">Βλάστη\u003C/span> · θυγάτηρ \u003Cbr id=\"al6-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>μητρὶ · εὐσεβεσ-\u003Cbr id=\"al7-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">7\u003C/span>τάτῃ · ἔποισε \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>ΔΑΙΜΟΣΙ\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>ΧΘΟΝΙΟΙΣ\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"\n                        Καιλία\n                        ·\n                        Ἑορτὴ\n                    \">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Καιλία\">ΚΑΙΛΙΑ\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Ἑορτὴ\">ΕΟΡΤΗ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>ΕΒΙΩΣΕΕΤΗΟ\u003Cbr id=\"al5-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Βλάστη\">ΒΛΑΣΤΗ\u003C/span>ΘΥΓΑΤΗΡ\u003Cbr id=\"al6-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>ΜΗΤΡΙΕΥΣΕΒΕΣ\u003Cbr id=\"al7-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">7\u003C/span>ΤΑΤΗΕΠΟΙΣΕ\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003223_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic003223_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003223.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic003223-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cp>  \u003C/p>\u003Cp>  \u003C/p>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>To the underworld spirits. Kailia Heorte lived for 70 years. Blaste, her daughter, made this for a devoted mother.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>Italian translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">Serena Agodi\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>Agli Spiriti sotterranei. Kailia Heorte ha vissuto per 70 anni. Blaste, sua figlia, ha fatto questo per la madre devota.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The phrasing of this text, with the unusual Δαίμοσι χθονίοις (one other Sicilian instance, IG XIV.294, from Alcamo), instead of the more normal Θεοῖς Καταχθονίοις (both imitating the Latin Dis Manibus), the uncommon ἐβίωσε instead of ἔζησε (‘she lived’, Latin vixit), and the unusual form ἔποισε (‘she made’, usually ἐποίησε, Latin fecit) all suggest the influence of typical Latin formulaic construction (compare nos. 18-21). Both Heorte and Blaste are rare names, mostly found in the eastern Mediterranean in the imperial period, but each is attested once also in Siracusa. Given that Kailia is the Latin Caelia, it is possible that Heorte is intended as a translation of the Latin Festa.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> 65 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Libertini 1931 46 no.11 = Libertini (1981) 96 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001870\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001870\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence.  \u003C/div>",[196,199,202,205,207,210,213],{"id":197,"html":198},"editions","\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>Δαίμοσι \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>χθονίοις \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"\n                        Καιλία\n                        ·\n                        Ἑορτὴ\n                    \">  \u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Καιλία\">Καιλία\u003C/span> · \u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Ἑορτὴ\">Ἑορτὴ\u003C/span>  \u003C/span> · \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>ἐβίωσε · ἔτη · ο’ \u003Cbr id=\"al5-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Βλάστη\">Βλάστη\u003C/span> · θυγάτηρ \u003Cbr id=\"al6-interpretive\">\u