 translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">Serena Agodi\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>Agli Spiriti sotterranei. Kailia Heorte ha vissuto per 70 anni. Blaste, sua figlia, ha fatto questo per la madre devota.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":208,"html":209},"commentary","\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The phrasing of this text, with the unusual Δαίμοσι χθονίοις (one other Sicilian instance, IG XIV.294, from Alcamo), instead of the more normal Θεοῖς Καταχθονίοις (both imitating the Latin Dis Manibus), the uncommon ἐβίωσε instead of ἔζησε (‘she lived’, Latin vixit), and the unusual form ἔποισε (‘she made’, usually ἐποίησε, Latin fecit) all suggest the influence of typical Latin formulaic construction (compare nos. 18-21). Both Heorte and Blaste are rare names, mostly found in the eastern Mediterranean in the imperial period, but each is attested once also in Siracusa. Given that Kailia is the Latin Caelia, it is possible that Heorte is intended as a translation of the Latin Festa.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":211,"html":212},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> 65 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Libertini 1931 46 no.11 = Libertini (1981) 96 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001870\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001870\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  ",{"id":214,"html":215},"license"," Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence.  ",[217,220],{"id":218,"lang":115,"html":219},"edition-interpretive","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>Δαίμοσι \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>χθονίοις \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenum